Equities are extremely over-valued (PG @ 62PE!), having failed to account for the risks of unprecedented systemic damage already sustained, with myriad unknowns yet to come. Our generation has never experienced such an uncertain wild card like a major pandemic, and this extreme level of uncertainty is toxic for markets. Current optimism is misplaced, when in reality, the wreckage of Main Street will severely impact corporate activity. Add to this civil and geopolitical conflict, and a surge in new cases resulting from large recreational and protest gatherings. Almost every expert has added the caveat "all bets are off if a 2nd wave". Since we are somewhere near halftime of the first wave, having never fully appreciated the extent of the current situation and soon-to-be-realized damage, people are making grand assumptions based on grossly incomplete understandings.
